description: TEHRAN – The two candidates competing in the July 5 presidential runoff, Saeed Jalili and Masoud Pezeshkian, have acknowledged the decline in voter participation for the first round of the snap presidential election, a decrease of 10% from the 50% turnout seen in 2021.
title: Candidates address decreased voter turnout in first presidential debate before runoff

description: TEHRAN - In a note, Kayhan addressed the attention of America to Iran's election. It wrote: Western political and media circles follow all Iranian elections with sensitivity and hope that the process of the increase of Iran's power during the presidency of Raisi does not continue.
title: West fears the continuation of the process of strengthening Iran

description: TEHRAN - Over 100,000 Iranians living outside the country cast their ballots in the first round of Iran's presidential election on June 28, according to Alireza Salimi, a member of the executive committee of the election.
title: Over 100,000 Iranians abroad cast votes in Iran's presidential election

description: TEHRAN – Tehran, the capital of Iran, is set to host the upcoming Asian–African Legal Consultative Organization (AALCO) conference, focusing on the prevention and countering of terrorism.
title: Tehran to host AALCO conference on countering terrorism

description: TEHRAN – On the 36th anniversary of the tragic downing of an Iranian passenger plane by a U.S. Navy guided-missile cruiser in the Persian Gulf, resulting in the death of all 290 people on board, the Iranian Foreign Ministry has issued a strong condemnation of the United States' long history of human rights violations.
title: Iran condemns U.S. human rights record on 36th anniversary of downed passenger plane

description: TEHRAN – The Secretary of Iran’s High Council for Human Rights has announced the establishment of a special judicial complex in Tehran province dedicated to handling international lawsuits and crimes.
title: Iran to establish special judicial complex for international crimes

description: TEHRAN-The 20th edition of the Tehran Auction focusing on modern and contemporary Iranian art is set to be held on July 5 at the Parsian Azadi Hotel in Tehran.
title: 20th Tehran Auction to present modern, contemporary Iranian art

description: TEHRAN- A select exhibition of 600 artistic works created by artists from various fields to pay tribute to President Raisi and his companions has been put on display at the Aali Gallery of Tehran's Art Bureau.
title: “Servants of the Nation" exhibition underway in Tehran

description: TEHRAN- A Persian translation of American writer Alex Finlay’s “The Night Shift” has recently been published by Amut Publications in Tehran.
title: “The Night Shift” at Iranian bookstores

description: TEHRAN – The spokesperson for the Iranian Foreign Ministry has condemned the severe and brutal actions of the Israeli military against Palestinians in Gaza, describing them as "unspeakable" and stressing that remaining silent on these atrocities is against the conscience of humanity.
title: Iran condemns global silence on Israeli aggression in Gaza

description: TEHRAN-An adaptation of Fyodor Dostoyevsky’s “The Gentle Spirit” is on stage at Book Garden Theater in Tehran.
title: Adaptation of Dostoyevsky’s “The Gentle Spirit” on Tehran stage

description: Israeli far-right minister Bezalel Smotrich has slammed a reported plan to re-supply the Gaza Strip with electricity, which Israel has cut off from the Palestinian enclave for nearly nine months.
title: Lieberman: Deny Gaza water, electricity

description: TEHRAN- Some of the Persian Gulf Arab states stand accused of complicity in Israel’s brutal onslaught on the Gaza Strip over their ties with the Tel Aviv regime.
title: Arab states’ tangled web of deceit

description: TEHRAN – Iran is waiting for the perfect opportunity to carry out the sequel to Operation True Promise, which pummeled several Israeli military bases in the occupied territories on April 14, said a high-ranking Iran Revolution Guard Corps official during a gathering with families of the Gaza war victims.
title: Iran waiting for the opportunity to conduct ‘Operation True Promise II’: Senior commander

description: TEHRAN – An advisor to Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Khamenei issued a stark warning in a recent interview with British media: any Israeli attack on Lebanon would trigger a decisive response from Iran and the entire Axis of Resistance in support of Hezbollah.
title: Iran has Hezbollah's back

description: The leader of the illegal Israeli settlements in the occupied West Bank has announced the death of Major Nadav Noler of Israel’s 8th Brigade of the 121st Battalion in Gaza.
title: 674 Israeli soldiers killed in Gaza

description: TEHRAN- The Palestinian resistance in Gaza continues to confront Israeli occupation forces for the 270th day in various parts of the Strip. The latest defensive operations have resulted in confirmed casualties among Israeli soldiers and damage to their vehicles.
title: Gaza resistance steadfast after 270 days

description: The Palestinian Education Ministry said 8,672 students have been killed and 14,583 others injured since the start of the Israeli aggression on October 7 against the Gaza Strip and the West Bank.
title: Israel has killed nearly 8,700 Palestinian students since Oct. 7

description: Israel’s evacuation order from the east of Khan Younis shows its inability to achieve its goal of eliminating Hamas and its intent to exhaust the population, Luciano Zaccara, a professor at Qatar University’s Gulf Studies Center, told Al Jazeera.
title: Israel wants to exhaust Palestinians with evacuation orders

description: TEHRAN - Two hundred and seventy days have passed since the start of the military operation and the horrible crimes of the Zionists in the Gaza Strip. This terrible tragedy has set unprecedented records in terms of the volume and depth of brutality committed in contemporary history.
title: 270 days of war and crime against Gaza

description: TEHRAN - The ancient city of Rey, which is now part of the Iranian capital, has received a boost in funding aimed at preserving its cultural and historical landmarks.
title: New funds to help protect Rey’s cultural heritage
Golestan Palace welcomes expert assessment of museum artifacts

description: TEHRAN - In an age dominated by AI-assisted graphic design, the ancient Persian art of Tazhib offers a compelling counterbalance, emphasizing patience, precision, and a deep connection to tradition.
title: Tazhib: an ancient yet reviving illumination art

description: TEHRAN – On Monday, Iran launched its first-ever tourism roadshow in the Vietnamese capital of Hanoi, aiming to boost bilateral tourism ties.
title: Iran debuts tourism roadshow in Vietnam

description: TEHRAN - In a tribute to the late Dr. Mahmoud Hessabi, the revered father of physics in Iran, his paternal home and its surrounding park has been restored, blending a celebration of the late scientist’s legacy with the preservation of Tehran’s historical heritage.
title: Dr. Hessabi’s paternal home ready to welcome visitors

description: As Iran approaches its run-off presidential election on July 5, the national tourism sector, which has rarely been addressed during recent debates, faces a pivotal moment.
title: Tourism and cultural heritage: a dual mandate for Iran’s next president

description: The long-term survival of Goitered gazelles in central Iran has been threatened because of the isolation of existing populations and genetic threats.
title: Goitered gazelle, a vulnerable species

description: TEHRAN – Attending the 40th Annual Science Olympiad Tournament at Michigan State University, Iranian students managed to win a bronze medal and two diplomas of honor.
title: Iranian students succeed at Science Olympiad 2024

description: TEHRAN –The 29th Technical Meeting of the G5 Forum was held in Tehran today with the theme of boosting health tourism among member states.
title: Tehran plays host to 29th G5 meeting

description: TEHRAN –A total of 573 earthquakes have been recorded across the country over the past calendar month that ended on June 19, according to the seismological networks of the Institute of Geophysics of the University of Tehran.
title: Over 570 earthquakes occur in a month

description: TEHRAN – Through financing 110 billion rials (about 184 million dollars) over the past three years, the share of benefactors in building schools has increased by 300 percent.
title: Benefactors sharply increase contribution to building schools

description: The 24th Meeting of the Council of Heads of State of the Shanghai Cooperation Organization (SCO) in Kazakhstan from July 3 to 4, 2024, will take place at a crucial juncture for the regional organization as the economies of the developing world are bolstering their efforts to coordinate their policies on a wide range of global issues, including rising security tensions, mounting protectionism in the world's economies, and intensifying competition in high-tech space.‬
title: SCO to drive economic co-op of developing countries in Eurasia

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Acting President Mohammad Mokhber has said the establishment of the International North-South Transit Corridor (INSTC) has a great impact on the promotion of cooperation between Iran and Kazakhstan, as well as other countries in the region.
title: North-South Corridor to boost Iran-Kazakhstan ties: Mokhber

description: TEHRAN- The head of National Land and Housing Organization of Iran said 48,000 hectares of land have been allocated to the implementation of the National Housing Movement in urban regions, IRNA reported.
title: 48,000 ha of land allocated to National Housing Movement

description: TEHRAN – The issuance of investment guarantees at Iran’s Small Industries Investment Guarantee Institute increased three times in the previous Iranian calendar year (ended on March 19), an official with the institute said.
title: Issuance of industrial investment guarantees triples in a year

description: TEHRAN - Iran has risen to become the fourth largest oil exporter within the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) due to a surge in oil production and sales.
title: Iran becomes 4th largest oil exporter in OPEC: report

description: TEHRAN - The trade exchanges between Iran and Turkey in the first five months of 2024 reached $2.3 billion, showing a five percent increase compared to the same month last year.
title: Iran-Turkey trade reaches $2.3b in 5 months

description: TEHRAN – Iranian men and women teams won the titles of the World Taekwondo World Cup Team Championships Series in Chuncheon, Korea.
title: Iranian taekwondo teams champions of World Cup Team Championships
Tehran Times' journalist speaks to CGTN

description: TEHRAN – Iran lost to Vietnam in straight sets (25-18, 25-16, 25-19) in the 2024 Asian Women’s U20 Volleyball Championship at the Jiangmen Sports Center Gymnasium on Tuesday.
title: Iran start 2024 Asian Women’s U20 Volleyball Championship on low note

description: TEHRAN – Iran Post has unveiled a new commemorative stamp to honor Para archer Sareh Javanmardi.
title: Iran Post unveils stamp featuring Para archer Sareh Javanmardi
